Description:
The pointname file name of PCS data.
| Default=pcsnames.dat.
| If USE_ALTERNATE_POINTNAMES <> 0, this file is read.

| When true, spline fitting is used to obtain constraints at the times that equilibria are requested.
| When false, the constraints are set to the nearest time that a measurement was made.
"Delta time between slices to analyze(?) in ms. (Does this override interactive input?)"

area where following input files are to be found, n1coil.d3d, ccoil.d3d, btcomp.d3d, dcoef.dat, fitweight.dat, sxr94.dat, efithelp.txt, limiter files and snap files. default = /link/efit/ (UNIX), sys$d3efit (VAX)
Number of time steps? (Does this override interactive input?)
"| Switch to turn on magnetic compensation for contributions due to C coil currents.
The input value for this parameter is not used.
"| Switch to turn on magnetic compensation for contributions due to I coil currents.
Scale factor for column in response matrix corresponding to difference in z position from 0?
destination for output EQDSK files if ISTORE = 1, default = /link/store/
area where Green's function tables and the configuration file mhdin.dat (and pcsnames.dat if used) are to be found. default = /link/efit/ (UNIX), lao$efund (VAX)
Start time(?) in ms. (Does this override interactive input?)
Maximum MSE beam offset time, in milliseconds.
If non-zero, PCS data specified in file ALTERNATE_POINTNAME_FILE are used.

When true, the data used to form constraints will be the same regardless of how many timeslices are being loaded.  (One caveat is if the variable size limit is hit, not all data will be fetched - see ntims/npefit in the code.)  Setting this to false will restore the legacy data fetching.  Default = .true.
For the snap modes (3 & 7), write the k file, as if EFIT were run in mode 5 to get those k files, then mode 2 to get the equilibria.
